pageContext.claim: “President Obama, from what they tell me, was under a similar kind of a thing -- didn't give one letter. They didn't do anything. They didn't give one letter of the request. Many requests were made; they didn't give a letter.”
pageContext.analysis: False. The Obama administration turned over hundreds of thousands of pages of records to congressional oversight committees. In some cases, the Obama administration resisted requests but ultimately turned over records under judicial order.
